```class Solution {
public:
    int minSwaps(string s) {
        int n = s.size(), res = 0, cnt = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            cnt += s[i] == '[' ? 1 : -1;
            if (cnt < 0) {
                res += -cnt;
                cnt = 0;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses a single pass through the string, maintaining a count of the balance of opening and closing brackets. Whenever the count becomes negative, it means we need to swap a closing bracket with an opening bracket, so we increment the result and reset the count.

